            It's a strategic departure from traditional, siloed development cycles, moving towards a fluid, integrated, and highly efficient ecosystem. Unlike traditional development, which often involves manual hand-offs between development, testing, and operations, an automation-ready approach builds automation into every stage of the lifecycle.
          </p>
          
